According to the reliable, if somewhat dry, reports from the [FAS](/Foreign_Agricultural_Service) and the [USDA](/United_States_Department_of_Agriculture), [China](/China) held the undeniable position as the largest producer of pork in the world in 2020. Following in its wake were the collective nations of the [European Union](/European_Union) and the [United States](/United_States). Together, these three entities accounted for approximately 76% of the world's total pork production. It's a rather predictable hierarchy, isn't it? The sheer scale of it is almost... exhausting.

